    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/927a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A representative of the National City Bank of New York, Mr. R. L. Farnham, has
                    presented to the Department the following draft contract which he desired the
                    Department to cable to you for Michelena, who will receive instructions to lay
                    it before the Dominican Government.</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of the draft contract, in the same words as those of the
                    inclosure to the next preceding communication.]</p>
                <p>You will make it clear to the Dominican Government, in case Michelena presents
                    the contract, that the Department does not indicate, by transmitting it, that it
                    should be given preference over any more favorable offer, but has sent it merely
                    as an accommodation to the bankers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
